OL,3,CAlmost two thirds of unpaid carers
OL,4,Ctook on role due to no other options `
OL,5,Creport
OL,7,FAlmost two thirds of current and
OL,8,Fformer unpaid carers had no choice but
OL,9,Fto take up the role due to the lack of
OL,10,Fother options available, according to
OL,11,Fa large survey which also suggests the
OL,12,Fsituation has worsened over time.
OL,14,FIt is estimated there are 16.1 million
OL,15,Fcurrent or former unpaid carers in the
OL,16,FUK and the new report has suggested
OL,17,Fthe "poor quality and high cost of
OL,18,Fsocial care services" could be a
OL,19,Freason for people feeling left with no
OL,20,Fchoice but to become unpaid carers.
