OL,3,CAlmost two thirds of unpaid carers
OL,4,Ctook on role due to no other options `
OL,5,Creport
OL,7,FThe situation appears to have
OL,8,Fdeteriorated, the report released to
OL,9,Fcoincide with Carers Week stated, with
OL,10,Fpeople currently providing unpaid care
OL,11,Fmore likely than those who had
OL,12,Fpreviously done so to say taking up
OL,13,Fthe role was due to a lack of
OL,14,Falternatives, at 66% compared with 59%.
OL,16,FThe report, supported by other
OL,17,Forganisations including Age UK and the
OL,18,FCarers Trust, was based on polling of
OL,19,Falmost 6,500 UK adults in early April,
OL,20,F30% of whom were either current or
OL,21,Fformer unpaid carers.
