OL,4,Ctook on role due to no other options `
OL,5,Creport
OL,7,FThe higher proportion of current
OL,8,Fcompared to former unpaid carers
OL,9,Freporting a lack of other options
OL,10,F"suggests that the alternative care
OL,11,Fand support options may have reduced
OL,12,Fover time, forcing more people to take
OL,13,Fon a caring role now than they would
OL,14,Fhave done before", the authors said.
OL,16,FThey added: "The lack of alternative
OL,17,Fcare options available, the poor
OL,18,Fquality and high cost of social care
OL,19,Fservices could be reasons why people
OL,20,Ffeel they have no choice on taking on
OL,21,Fa caring role.
